ed to update the metadata. It looks like the dynamic access report coverage uses a native image called `reflection-calls.json`, which includes a call site list and outputs from a runtime agent. This has me wondering if I should look into the available tooling for handling this. A deeper dive into the tools might yield a solution to improve coverage reporting, especially regarding dynamic access scenarios. Let's see what I find!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_4vNiinE1jIZzXcokTl2LAiYL|fc_0db78ac3875b81430169f009a0f61c819e99a4175968bdfd71", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"dynamic-access-coverage|reflection-calls|coveredCalls|TrackDynamicAccess|generateDynamicAccessReport\" -n build-logic gradle tests | head -200", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2561, "output": 1334, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53559, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777338763198, "responseId": "resp_0db78ac3875b81430169f0098be070819ebca57b9ed53d2528"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_4vNiinE1jIZzXcokTl2LAiYL|fc_0db78ac3875b81430169f009a0f61c819e99a4175968bdfd71", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "rg: build-logic: No such file or directory (os error 2)\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtilsTests.java:31:                        \"-H:TrackDynamicAccess=path=\" + firstJar.toAbsolutePath(),\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtilsTests.java:33:                        \"-H:TrackDynamicAccess=path=\" + secondJar.toAbsolutePath(),\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/DynamicAccessUtils.java:20:    private static final String TRACK_DYNAMIC_ACCESS_PREFIX = \"-H:TrackDynamicAccess=path=\";\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalv