"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Refining testing methods**\\n\\nThe statement feels too broad and incorrect. I believe we need proper tests. There seems to be a limitation with the dynamic report implementation regarding line breaks. Perhaps the only approach is to adjust the local test project. While the task focuses specifically on tests, we might refine the build.gradle file to accommodate coverage reporting. However, I wonder if my previous adjustment was too hacky. Maybe adding a generated source overlay could be a better solution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating bug fix approach**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I could patch `LibraryStatsSupport` to account for the nearest previous covered line for synthetic `class$`. It sounds broad but could be a meaningful fix. Currently, when using `parsedFrame.method` for `class$`, JaCoCo filters synthetic lines, so mapping to the previous covered line might be useful. However, since the user task specifies focusing only on the active class, I wonder if broadening that scope is the right move. Adding a dynamic access report source map doesn’t seem ideal either.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering build.gradle modifications**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I could modify the `build.gradle` file after the report generation. If the XML has a specific line from `ApacheCatalogResolver.java`, I could insert a new line under certain conditions. However, altering the build logic for just one class might seem clunky. Maybe it’s better to patch the TCK report parser to treat certain lines as covered instead. That would address an issue with old javac class literal line-splitting but could be a bit broad.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting outputs**\\n\\nI'm thinking about our tests and whether there could be differences in the CI, particularly after looking at line 122 of our report. I can use regex to check for line nr=\\\"122\\\" with ci>0. However, I've noticed the XML output has no indentation, which might complicate things. I definitely need to inspect the surrounding context to find out what's going on.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9tm3sGVj8aEXd1MVCdBzTbnk|fc_0db78ac3875b81430169f009c4f184819ea840427970ec4ce9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\np='tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build/reports/jacoco/test/jacocoTestReport.xml'\ns=open(p).read()\nidx=s.find('name=\"ApacheCatalogResolver.java\"')\nprint(s[idx:idx+500])\nPY", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1734, "output": 1956, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 60522, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777338791859, "responseId": "resp_0db78ac3875b81430169f009a881a4819e9d2bf8ed1b03e8cb"}}
